<tr>
<td width=53 valign=top rowspan=2 style='background: url(intr/2leftfill.png)'><img width=53 height=72 src='intr/2topleft.png'></td>
<td align=right width=100% style='height: 32px; background: url(intr/2topfill.png)'><nobr>
<a href='guis'><img width=60 height=32 alt='GUIs' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/guis.png'></a><a href='timelines'><img width=86 height=32 alt='Timelines' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/timelines.png'></a><a href='screenshots'><img width=112 height=32 alt='Screenshots' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/screenshots.png'></a><a href='icons'><img width=49 height=32 alt='Icons' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/icons.png'></a><a href='sounds'><img width=69 height=32 alt='Sounds' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/sounds.png'></a><a href='splashes'><img width=90 height=32 alt='Splashes' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/splashes.png'></a><a href='apps'><img width=55 height=32 alt='Applications' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/apps.png'></a><a href='ads'><img width=56 height=32 alt='Ads' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/ads-top5.png'></a><a href='videos'><img width=56 height=32 alt='Videos' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/videos-top5.png'></a><a href='articles'><img width=62 height=32 alt='Articles' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/articles-top5.png'></a><a href='books'><img width=53 height=32 alt='Books' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/books-top5.png'></a><a href='tutorials'><img width=78 height=32 alt='Tutorials' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/tutorials-top5.png'></a><a href='extras'><img width=96 height=32 alt='Extras' border=0 src='intr/2tabs/extras.png'></a></nobr></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top width=100% height=100% style='background: url(intr/background2.png) #f2f2f2; padding-top: 30px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 10px; padding-bottom: 30px;'>
<table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr height=20><td><nobr><a href='tutorials/macintoshbasics50'><img width=9 height=20 style='margin-right: 10px' border=0 alt='Go back' src='intr/2captions/goback.png'><img border=0 alt='Macintosh Basics' hspace=0 src='intr/2captions/macintoshbasics.png'></a></td><td valign=top height=20><img width=19 height=20 align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3toprise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 rowspan=3 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3topfill.png) white top repeat-x'><img border=0 alt='Creating a document' style='margin-left: 3px; margin-top: 12px; margin-right: 10px' src='intr/3captions/creatingadocument.png'></td><td valign=top style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)' height=20><img width=12 height=20 align=right hspace=0 src='intr/3topright.png'></td></tr><tr><td valign=top width=20 style='background: url(intr/3topleftfill.png) top repeat-x'><img width=20 height=20 hspace=0 src='intr/3topleft.png'></td><td valign=top><img align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3topleftrise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td width=20 height=50 style='background: url(intr/3leftfill.png) white left repeat-y;'><img width=20 height=1 src='intr/3leftfill.png'></td><td width=100% class=box3text style='background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 15px; '>

<p>
<table class=reg cellpadding=10 cellspacing=0 border=0>

<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/001.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You can use your Macintosh to create different
kinds of documents: letters, memos, drawings,
or spreadsheets, for example. In this section,
you&rsquo;ll learn how to create a memo.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/002.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
To create your memo, you&rsquo;ll use a program
that is stored on your Hard Disk. To use the
program, you need to OPEN the Hard Disk,
just as you&rsquo;d open a file cabinet to
use things stored there. To open the
Hard Disk: First, click the Hard Disk icon.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/003.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Good. Notice that the Hard Disk icon is
now filled in, or SELECTED. You still need to
tell the Macintosh to open it.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/004.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
To open the Hard Disk icon, choose the
Open command from the File menu:
<ol>
<li>Point to the File menu title.
<li>Press and hold down the button.
<li>Drag through the list of command. They
will become HIGHLIGHTED as you drag through
them.
<li>Release the button when Open is highlighted.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/005.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Good. When you open the Hard Disk icon, a WINDOW
appears that lets you see what&rsquo;s stored on
the Hard Disk.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/006.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
The TITLE BAR of the window displays the
window&rsquo;s name. The icons you see in the window
represent things that are stored on the
Hard Disk.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/007.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
On the Hard Disk, there is a SYSTEM FOLDER,
containing programs that run your Macintosh.
You&rsquo;ll learn more about folders later.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/008.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
The Hard Disk also contains MemoWriter, a sample
APPLICATION PROGRAM. You use application programs
to create documents &ndash; such as letters, drawings,
or budgets.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/009.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
To use MemoWriter to write your memo, you need
to open it. Remember that opening an icon
is a two-step process:
<ol>
<li>First, click the MemoWriter icon to select
it. The icon will become highlighted.
<li>Then choose Open from the File menu.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/010.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Good. Now you&rsquo;ve opened the MemoWriter program
and you see a window called &ldquo;Untitled.&rdquo; This
is your new document. It&rsquo;s like a blank piece
of paper.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/011.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You are going to use this program to write
a memo to a co-worker, arranging a lunch
meeting.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/012.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Click the right arrow, and I&rsquo;ll start the memo
for you.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/013.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Now, you need to add your name to the memo.
<ol>
<li>Move the pointer to the space to the right
of &ldquo;From:&rdquo;
<li>Then click at that location. This tells
The Macintosh where you want new text to
appear.
<li>Type your first name. Use the Delete key
on your keyboard to backspace over mistakes.
<li>When you&rsquo;re done, click the right arrow
to move on.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/014.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Next, add some text at the end of the memo:
<ol>
<li>Click below the word &ldquo;about&rdquo; to set the
insertion point.
<li>Type the words: How about 12:00 at Swanky&rsquo;s?
<li>Click the right arrow when you&rsquo;re done.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/015.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Now you need to SAVE your memo on a disk,
so that it isn&rsquo;t lost when you turn off the
computer. To save a document, you give it
a name and tell the computer where to store
it.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/016.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
To save your memo, you choose the Save command
from the File menu:
<ol>
<li>Point to the File menu title.
<li>Press and hold down the button.
<li>Drag through the list of commands.
<li>Release the button when Save is highlighted.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/017.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
When you choose Save, a DIALOG BOX appears.
The Macintosh uses a dialog box to request more
information from you. This dialog box lets you
name and save your document.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/018.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
The word &ldquo;Untitled&rdquo; in the TEXT BOX is highlighted.
This means that the word will be replaced by
whatever you type.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/019.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
To name your memo, type Memo to Sandy. Because
&ldquo;Untitled&rdquo; is already highlighted, all you
have to do is start typing. You don&rsquo;t even
have to click first. When you&rsquo;re done, click the
right arrow.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/020.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Good. Now, to save this document: Click the
Save button.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/021.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
After you save your document, the new name
appears in the title bar of the document
window.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/022.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Now that you&rsquo;ve saved your memo, you can quit
the MemoWriter program. To quit the program,
you choose the Quit command from the File
menu.
<ol>
<li>Move the pointer to the File menu title.
<li>Press and hold down the button.
<li>Drag through the menu until Quit is highlighted.
<li>Release the button.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/023.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
And now you are back at the desktop. You can
see that your Memo to Sandy is now stored
on the Hard Disk.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/024.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
In this section, you&rsquo;ve learned about creating
a document. Click the right arrow to practice
what you&rsquo;ve learned.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/025.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You are going to practice creating a new memo
and saving it on the Hard Disk.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/026.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Open the Hard Disk icon. Remember: opening an
icon is a two-step process. You need to select
the icon before you open it.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/027.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Now open the MemoWriter application program.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/028.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Here&rsquo;s the memo, already started. All you
have to do is sign it.
<ol>
<li>Click to set the insertion pointer on the
line below &ldquo;Sincerely.&rdquo;
<li>Type your name.
<li>Click the right arrow when you&rsquo;re done.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/029.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Now, save your memo and name it Memo to Jay.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/030.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Now, quit the program.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/031.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Here is your new document: Memo to Jay. 
(By the way, this tour does not save the work
you do in the practice sessions, so you won&rsquo;t
see Memo to Jay in later sections.)
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/macintoshbasics50/creatingadocument/032.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Good. You&rsquo;ve now completed &ldquo;Creating a Document.&rdquo;
</p></td></tr>
</table></p>

</td><td height=50 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'><img width=12 height=1 src='intr/3rightfill.png'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td height=30><img width=20 height=30 hspace=0 src='intr/3bottomleft.png'></td><td height=30 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3bottomfill.png)'></td><td height=30><img width=30 height=30 hspace=0 src='intr/3bottomclosed.png'></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></td></tr>

